==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forum
<hw>Fo"rum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Forums</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Fora</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L.; akin to <ets>foris</ets>, <ets>foras</ets>, out of doors. See
<er>Foreign</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A market place or public place
in Rome, where causes were judicially tried, and orations delivered to
the people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tribunal; a court; an assembly empowered to hear
and decide causes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He [Lord Camden] was . . . more eminent in the senate than in the
<qex>forum</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Brougham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forwaked</ent>⟦br⟧
